The discounted cash flow method (DCF) is an estimation method that values the investment based on its future cash flows. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{DCF}&=\dfrac{\text{Dividend}}{\text{Current Price}}+\text{Growth Rate}
\end{aligned}$$

On the other hand, the security market line (SML) method is a graphical and visual representation of the expected returns based on the systematic risk of the company. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{SML}&=\text{Risk-free rate} +\beta \times(\text{Market rate}-\text{Risk-free rate})
\end{aligned}$$
